> [{quoted}](name=Skorch,realm=NA,application-id=3ErqAdtq,discussion-id=aIWQ7FEg,comment-id=0007,timestamp=2017-12-25T17:52:06.588+0000)
>
> I feel like part of issue is even though we are several weeks in there are still balances to change and metas to form, i still havent found a champ that was even bad after new runes. So because of that people dont even know what meta is, how they should play. Is the meta 4 man bot+turret+drag still? or is it cheese top? I say in 1 or so month metas will start forming and the overall craziness (not balance, that is always being changed) will start going down.

There's a very clear meta: "Everyone pick the longest range champion you can to avoid taking any damage because if you get hit by anything you're dead (unless your name is Alistar)."

That's why a standard game looks like this:
{{champion:17}} vs {{champion:126}} 
